                <h3 class="my-3">How to Reach</h3>
                <h4 class="my-4">By Road</h4>
                <p>The nearest large town is Kahalgaon, about 13 km away. It is accessible via an 11 km motorable road from NH-80 at Anadipur, near Kahalgaon.</p>
                <h4 class="my-4">By Rail</h4>
                <p>Bikramshila and Kahalgaon railway stations are located on the Sahibganj Loop line, close to the site.</p>
                <h4 class="my-4">By River</h4>
                <p>River cruises from Kolkata to Varanasi now include stops at the Vikramashila ruins, offering a unique way to visit the site.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3 class="my-3">Popular Culture</h3>
                <h4 class="my-4">Recognition</h4>
                <p>An Indian Railways train, Vikramshila Express (Train No. 12367/12368), runs from Anand Vihar, Delhi to Bhagalpur, Bihar, commemorating this historical site.</p>
                <h4 class="my-4">Annual Event</h4>
                <p>The Vikramashila Mahotsav is held annually in February, celebrating the cultural and historical significance of the site.</p>
